MALE GENITALIA: Left paramere somewhat narrow and angled dorsally with hook-shaped hypophysis, hypophysis somewhat long, its apex rounded; sensory lobe with noticeable process, process short (
Fig. 4A
), lateral tooth small in lateral view (
Fig. 4B
); right paramere with somewhat short and thick hypophysis, its apex blunt (
Fig. 4C
); endosoma membranous with one long spicule and three sclerites; 
sp
as long as membranous lobe, broader from subapical part; 
ls
I thick and tapered to apex; 
ls
II with tiny spinules in only upper and lateral part; 
ms
bifurcated, shorter than membranous lobe, length of each part different, one part short (
Fig. 4
D–F).

